<dl id="n10145n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10145n">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10145n"> 145(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> big eye (greed)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">And this would be delightfully all right provided the negro welcomed us as a letter postman&mdash;God&apos;s postman bringing God&apos;s letter. Alas! he thinks we are parcels postmen, and any of the humblest ameliorations of civilisation about us develop in the negro that <mark>avarice known locally as &ldquo;the big eye.&rdquo;</mark> <small> Daniel Crawford, <a name="DCTB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DCTB"><cite title="source">Thinking Black</cite></a> (1912) 216</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
